claim: Flublok contains 45 micrograms (mcg) of HA per strain vs 15 mcg of HA per strain in a standard-dose influenza vaccine.
explanation: Partial title page of a journal article from Vaccine (Elsevier), showing the journal header and the beginning of the article title: “Protective efficacy of a trivalent recombinant hemagglutinin protein vaccine (FluBlok®) against influenza in healthy adults…”. The image only shows the article header and title; it does not provide any information on HA microgram content per strain and therefore does not support the claim. Note: Limited view of only the title page; no dosing details visible.
